title: Align Tally::approval() with VoteTally trait semantics
doc:
- audience: Runtime Dev
  description: |
    `Tally::approval()` in `pallet-conviction-voting` now returns `Perbill::zero()`
    when no aye or nay votes have been cast, consistent with the `pallet-referenda`
    test mock. The `VoteTally::approval()` trait doc is also updated
    to document this expected behavior.
crates:
- name: pallet-conviction-voting
  bump: patch
- name: frame-support
  bump: patch